OL,6,FChief Inspector Rob Cheeseman, head of
OL,7,FRoads Policing, said: "The arrest data
OL,8,Ffor the first eight weeks of 2024
OL,9,Fshows that drink and drug driving
OL,10,Fremains a major problem on our roads,
OL,11,Fdespite the well known risks.J"It
OL,12,Fshould also dispel the misconception
OL,13,Fthat enforcement activity only goes on
OL,14,Fduring the Christmas period when media
OL,15,Fattention peaks. To be clear: those
OL,16,Fwho make the reckless choice to drink
OL,17,For drug drive, day or night, should
OL,18,Fexpect to get caught.J"I would like to
OL,19,Facknowledge the hard work of our teams
OL,20,F- including the Special Constabulary,
OL,21,Fwho volunteer their time - who are all
OL,22,Fworking tirelessly to keep our roads
OL,23,Fsafe."
